181
00:09:15,540 --> 00:09:17,000
What were you guys saying just now?

182
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:18,820
Nothing.

183
00:09:23,660 --> 00:09:25,240
Ding Zhi Tong.

184
00:09:27,180 --> 00:09:28,740
Don't be angry.

185
00:09:28,740 --> 00:09:29,860
We just know each other well.

186
00:09:29,860 --> 00:09:31,220
Sometimes, they speak without thinking.

187
00:09:31,220 --> 00:09:33,540
Don't take it to heart. I'll scold them later.

188
00:09:33,540 --> 00:09:35,520
You still defend them after all they did?

189
00:09:35,520 --> 00:09:38,280
They act nice to your face, but do you know what they say behind your back?

190
00:09:38,280 --> 00:09:40,900
They say you'll never make good shoes.

191
00:09:40,900 --> 00:09:42,460
Really?

192
00:09:43,460 --> 00:09:44,960
Yes.

193
00:09:50,020 --> 00:09:52,340
Why are you still smiling?

194
00:09:54,220 --> 00:09:55,860
Ding Zhi Tong.

195
00:09:58,180 --> 00:09:59,940
What?

196
00:09:59,940 --> 00:10:02,040
Are you concerned about me?

197
00:10:14,540 --> 00:10:16,240
You're crazy.

198
00:10:16,240 --> 00:10:19,300
Ding Zhi Tong, thank you.

199
00:10:41,840 --> 00:10:45,420
Professor Qin, this is for you.

200
00:10:45,420 --> 00:10:47,800
Your voice sounds a little hoarse.

201
00:10:47,800 --> 00:10:49,600
This is good for soothing your throat.

202
00:10:49,600 --> 00:10:51,460
Are you openly bribing me?

203
00:10:51,460 --> 00:10:52,820
Of course not.

204
00:10:52,820 --> 00:10:55,620
You still teach us even while you're sick.

205
00:10:55,620 --> 00:10:57,580
I'm just showing my concern.

206
00:10:57,580 --> 00:11:00,460
Go ahead, what do you want?

207
00:11:00,460 --> 00:11:03,840
Then I'll be straight.

208
00:11:05,300 --> 00:11:06,940
I'd like you to take me

209
00:11:06,940 --> 00:11:10,660
to the finance networking event coming up.

210
00:11:10,660 --> 00:11:14,740
It's a large-scale event. Attendees need a plus-one.

211
00:11:14,740 --> 00:11:18,900
Well, I'm well-versed in finance, stocks, funds, trusts,

212
00:11:18,900 --> 00:11:21,900
and whatever else you can name.

213
00:11:21,900 --> 00:11:24,300
Besides, I'm great at socializing.

214
00:11:24,300 --> 00:11:27,340
I swear... I swear I won't embarrass you.

215
00:11:29,780 --> 00:11:31,960
That actually does makes sense.

216
00:11:32,620 --> 00:11:36,700
Moreover, we have a teacher-student relationship.

217
00:11:36,700 --> 00:11:41,220
Even if people find out, they'll only praise you

218
00:11:41,220 --> 00:11:43,580
for being a kind, selfless teacher.

219
00:11:43,580 --> 00:11:45,500
No one will overthink it,

220
00:11:45,500 --> 00:11:47,240
and it'll avoid any unnecessary gossip.

221
00:11:47,240 --> 00:11:50,720
Given all that, you might actually be the best choice.

222
00:11:50,720 --> 00:11:54,100
So... are you agreeing?

223
00:11:54,100 --> 00:11:56,120
I'll consider it.

224
00:11:56,940 --> 00:11:58,980
Thank you, Professor Qin!

225
00:11:58,980 --> 00:12:00,380
Please think it over.

226
00:12:00,380 --> 00:12:01,980
Yes!

227
00:12:06,300 --> 00:12:08,280
I have to admit,

228
00:12:08,280 --> 00:12:10,420
