Shoes.

264
00:13:26,440 --> 00:13:27,780
No.

265
00:13:27,780 --> 00:13:30,180
More accurately,

266
00:13:30,180 --> 00:13:33,140
it's the junk you were just talking about.

267
00:13:33,140 --> 00:13:34,500
Since you clearly disdain the shoes,

268
00:13:34,500 --> 00:13:36,420
I won't have you try them anymore.

269
00:13:36,420 --> 00:13:37,980
I'll take the shoes back.

270
00:13:37,980 --> 00:13:42,000
Wait, if you take them, what will we wear?

271
00:13:42,000 --> 00:13:44,160
That's your problem.

272
00:13:44,720 --> 00:13:46,740
- Come on, hurry. 
 - Gan Yang,

273
00:13:46,740 --> 00:13:49,260
did that girl say anything to you?

274
00:13:53,460 --> 00:13:55,260
She has nothing to do with this.

275
00:13:58,940 --> 00:14:01,660
- Gan Yang! 
 - Don't go after him.

276
00:14:15,460 --> 00:14:16,500
Hello?

277
00:14:16,500 --> 00:14:18,300
Ding Zhi Tong,

278
00:14:18,300 --> 00:14:21,420
thank you for helping me truly see those guys.

279
00:14:21,420 --> 00:14:24,460
Do you mean those guys on the track team?

280
00:14:28,680 --> 00:14:29,720
Are you okay?

281
00:14:29,720 --> 00:14:32,560
I'm fine. Don't worry.

282
00:14:32,560 --> 00:14:35,020
They're not worth feeling bad over.

283
00:14:35,020 --> 00:14:37,800
Exactly. I'm glad you think so.

284
00:14:42,080 --> 00:14:43,680
Gan Yang?

285
00:14:45,080 --> 00:14:47,320
Gan Yang? Why aren't you saying anything?

286
00:14:47,320 --> 00:14:49,060
Ding Zhi Tong.

287
00:14:50,780 --> 00:14:52,540
Thank you.

288
00:14:55,100 --> 00:14:57,600
You've already thanked me once.

289
00:14:58,220 --> 00:14:59,900
Don't mention it.

290
00:15:07,660 --> 00:15:11,040
   

291
00:15:14,700 --> 00:15:16,620
I've made comments on yesterday's assignment.

292
00:15:16,620 --> 00:15:17,920
Can someone help hand it out?

293
00:15:17,920 --> 00:15:19,520
I will.

294
00:15:22,900 --> 00:15:25,020
- Thanks. 
 - No problem.

295
00:15:26,460 --> 00:15:29,180
There's a finance networking event soon.

296
00:15:29,180 --> 00:15:31,760
All the attendees are major players in the industry.

297
00:15:31,760 --> 00:15:34,500
It's a great chance to gain insight at this event.

298
00:15:34,500 --> 00:15:38,240
And you can make connections to help with future job prospects.

299
00:15:38,240 --> 00:15:41,380
I happen to have an invitation here. 
    

300
00:15:41,380 --> 00:15:42,800
And I can take one person with me.

301
00:15:42,800 --> 00:15:45,460
To keep things fair, I've decided that

302
00:15:45,460 --> 00:15:48,470
whoever ranks first in the upcoming due diligence simulation

303
00:15:48,470 --> 00:15:50,120
can go with me.

304
00:15:50,120 --> 00:15:53,000
Professor, can guys participate, too?

305
00:15:53,000 --> 00:15:55,220
- Gender doesn't matter. 
 - Professor Qin.

306
00:15:55,220 --> 00:15:57,860
Do you disagree with my decision?

307
00:15:57,860 --> 00:15:58,940
Not at all.

308
00:15:58,940 --> 00:16:02,180
In that case, move a bit more quickly, please.

309
00:16:07,740 --> 00:16:09,460
Professor Qin.

310
00:16:10,200 --> 00:16:12,620
Don't you have something to say to me?

311
00:16:12,620 --> 00:16:14,380
Now that you mention it, I do.

312
00:16:14,380 --> 00:16:16,700
I had been struggling to find someone to take with me.

313
00:16:16,700 --> 00:16:18,560
Thanks for reminding me I can take a student.

314
00:16:18,560 --> 00:16:20,180
You tricked me?

315
00:16:20,180 --> 00:16:23,180
If you didn't want to take me, you could have just told me.

316
00:16:24,040 --> 00:16:25,840
Maybe you misunderstood.

317
00:16:25,840 --> 00:16:28,160
First, I agreed that I'd consider it,

318
00:16:28,160 --> 00:16:29,700
but I never promised you anything.

319
00:16:29,700 --> 00:16:32,140
Second, you made valid points,

320
00:16:32,140 --> 00:16:35,080
but you're not my only student.

321
00:16:35,740 --> 00:16:38,200
And last, the simulation hasn't even started yet.

322
00:16:38,200 --> 00:16:39,620
Are you saying you will eventually lose?

323
00:16:39,620 --> 00:16:42,000
Are you provoking me?

324
00:16:42,000 --> 00:16:43,660
I swear I will win.

325
00:16:43,660 --> 00:16:45,400
Watch and see!

326
00:16:53,640 --> 00:16:55,540
Hurry and wash a few more.

327
00:16:55,540 --> 00:16:57,960
Okay. Are you sure you know how to make it?

328
00:16:57,960 --> 00:17:00,800
Of course. You've tasted my cooking before.

329
00:17:00,800 --> 00:17:03,360
Since I can cook, I can make jam.

330
00:17:03,360 --> 00:17:05,760
Are cooking and jam-making the same?

331
00:17:05,760 --> 00:17:06,840
You'll see when you taste it.

332
00:17:06,840 --> 00:17:08,240
It will be good too.

333
00:17:08,240 --> 00:17:10,140
Delicious.

334
00:17:10,140 --> 00:17:12,060
- Add more sugar. 
 - Okay.

335
00:17:12,060 --> 00:17:14,420
I like sweet stuff.

336
00:17:21,720 --> 00:17:23,280
- Try it. 
 - You go first.

337
00:17:23,280 --> 00:17:24,060
- You've worked hard. 
 - I go first?

338
00:17:24,060 --> 00:17:25,520
Yes, you get the first bite.

339
00:17:25,520 --> 00:17:27,020
All right.

340
00:17:32,260 --> 00:17:34,880
Well, how is it? Is it good?

341
00:17:39,460 --> 00:17:40,940
No.

342
00:17:41,700 --> 00:17:43,160
It's terrible.

343
00:17:43,160 --> 00:17:44,200
No way.

344
00:17:44,200 --> 00:17:45,960
- Let me try it. 
 - It's awful.

345
00:17:45,960 --> 00:17:47,060
- Let me try it. 
 - You'd better not.

346
00:17:47,060 --> 00:17:48,340
Trust me, Pal. You'd better not.

347
00:17:48,340 --> 00:17:50,140
I don't believe you. Let me try.

348
00:17:50,140 --> 00:17:51,400
It's really bad.

349
00:17:51,400 --> 00:17:53,680
Just one small spoonful, okay?

350
00:17:53,680 --> 00:17:55,500
Fine, one small spoonful.

351
00:17:55,500 --> 00:17:57,400
Use this spoon.

352
00:17:59,180 --> 00:18:02,480
W-Wait. This is also a spoon.

353
00:18:20,300 --> 00:18:22,840
Who's there? Come out!

354
00:18:54,940 --> 00:18:56,580
That darned Qin Chang. 
    

355
00:18:56,580 --> 00:18:57,980
Old fashioned.

356
00:18:57,980 --> 00:19:00,500
I went out of my way to impress him.

357
00:19:00,500 --> 00:19:04,500
Seriously, when have I ever been so humiliated?

358
00:19:04,500 --> 00:19:06,060
You rotten man.

359
00:19:06,680 --> 00:19:08,520
Tong Tong, perfect timing.

360
00:19:08,520 --> 00:19:10,660
I say that Qin Chang has really gone too far!

361
00:19:10,660 --> 00:19:12,340
Ming Mei.

362
00:19:14,780 --> 00:19:16,900
Wait, what happened to your hand?

363
00:19:16,900 --> 00:19:18,860
I was so clumsy.

364
00:19:18,860 --> 00:19:21,340
I tripped on the way back.

365
00:19:21,340 --> 00:19:22,560
It should be okay.

366
00:19:22,560 --> 00:19:24,080
Does it hurt?

367
00:19:24,080 --> 00:19:26,580
- I'll take you to the clinic. Come on. 
 - No need for that.

368
00:19:26,580 --> 00:19:29,100
It's so late. Let's just disinfect it.

369
00:19:29,100 --> 00:19:31,480
- Do you have iodine? 
 - I do.

370
00:19:31,480 --> 00:19:33,560
Come on. Sit down.

371
00:19:34,040 --> 00:19:35,640
 Gan Yang. 

372
00:19:36,580 --> 00:19:38,220
Gan Yang?

373
00:19:43,620 --> 00:19:47,180
I can eat this delicious jam myself.

374
00:20:03,500 --> 00:20:05,780
Gan Yang!

375
00:20:07,780 --> 00:20:09,680
Why are you here?

376
00:20:09,680 --> 00:20:13,460
I made some plum jam and brought you some.

377
00:20:21,060 --> 00:20:22,960
I'll take this call.

378
00:20:24,080 --> 00:20:25,320
Hello? What do you want?

379
00:20:25,320 --> 00:20:28,320
Where did you hide the jam?

380
00:20:28,320 --> 00:20:30,820
- Do you even have a conscience? 
 - Shut up.

381
00:20:33,580 --> 00:20:34,960
Wrong number.

382
00:20:34,960 --> 00:20:37,400
You changed your ringtone?

383
00:20:39,060 --> 00:20:42,740
I thought that song was nice so I changed it.

384
00:20:43,920 --> 00:20:46,320
I can't believe you know archery, surfing,

385
00:20:46,320 --> 00:20:50,260
skiing, shoe design, and you can make jam.

386
00:20:52,720 --> 00:20:58,140
How did you know I ski, surf, and do archery?

387
00:20:59,200 --> 00:21:01,440
I found out by accident.

388
00:21:02,060 --> 00:21:04,460
Here, take the jam.

389
00:21:04,460 --> 00:21:06,120
Thanks.

390
00:21:07,720 --> 00:21:09,460
What happened to your hand?

391
00:21:09,460 --> 00:21:10,700
Nothing.

392
00:21:10,700 --> 00:21:13,660
The light didn't work on the path back to the dorm. I tripped and fell.

393
00:21:13,660 --> 00:21:14,840
It's fine.

394
00:21:14,840 --> 00:21:16,380
Thanks.

395
00:21:19,080 --> 00:21:21,540
Oh, be sure to keep it in the fridge.

396
00:21:21,540 --> 00:21:22,480
It tastes even better cold.

397
00:21:22,480 --> 00:21:24,700
Okay. I'll try that.

398
00:21:24,700 --> 00:21:26,560
- I'm going. 
 - Bye bye.

399
00:21:26,560 --> 00:21:28,140
Bye bye.

400
00:21:33,600 --> 00:21:35,480
The light doesn't work?

401
00:21:43,740 --> 00:21:46,840
Gan Yang, where did you hide the jam?

402
00:21:46,840 --> 00:21:48,940
- I ate it. 
 - I'm not talking to you anymore.

403
00:21:48,940 --> 00:21:49,920
I didn't even get one bite.

404
00:21:49,920 --> 00:21:51,600
Stop.

405
00:21:51,600 --> 00:21:53,000
Let's go ghost hunting tonight.

406
00:21:53,000 --> 00:21:55,320
What ghost?

407
00:22:10,180 --> 00:22:11,920
It's okay.

408
00:22:11,920 --> 00:22:14,520
It's just stray cats and dogs.

409
00:22:20,700 --> 00:22:22,920
- Shut up. 
 - Be quiet.

410
00:22:26,440 --> 00:22:27,540
Who's there?

411
00:22:27,540 --> 00:22:30,240
I see you. Come out!

412
00:22:30,240 --> 00:22:31,420
 Who's there? 

413
00:22:31,420 --> 00:22:33,360
Say something.

414
00:22:33,360 --> 00:22:34,560
Don't move.

415
00:22:34,560 --> 00:22:36,620
Keep your voice down.

416
00:22:38,040 --> 00:22:40,480
 We don't want anyone to see. 

417
00:22:40,480 --> 00:22:42,400
Speak louder. Say it louder.

418
00:22:42,400 --> 00:22:44,640
You're so bad. So annoying.

419
00:22:44,640 --> 00:22:46,360
 Don't touch me. 

420
00:22:46,360 --> 00:22:48,740
 Others will see. 

421
00:22:56,680 --> 00:22:58,440
- What are you trying? 
 - What are you guys doing?

422
00:22:58,440 --> 00:23:00,600
Why are you following Ding Zhi Tong?

423
00:23:00,600 --> 00:23:01,800
I don't know what you're saying.

424
00:23:01,800 --> 00:23:04,160
You don't know what I'm saying?

425
00:23:04,160 --> 00:23:06,460
- Wang Yi. 
 - We knew you wouldn't admit it.

426
00:23:06,460 --> 00:23:08,480
We already set up security cameras here.

427
00:23:08,480 --> 00:23:11,480
If I send this video to your coach,

428
00:23:11,480 --> 00:23:14,280
your career is over.

429
00:23:16,300 --> 00:23:18,060
Don't, Director Gan.

430
00:23:18,060 --> 00:23:20,200
I was wrong. Aren't we buddies?

431
00:23:20,200 --> 00:23:22,340
I just wanted to scare her. That's all.

432
00:23:22,340 --> 00:23:24,680
"Scare her"?

433
00:23:24,680 --> 00:23:29,080
Li Fei, we can keep the video a secret.

434
00:23:29,080 --> 00:23:31,800
But stalking won't just be forgiven.

435
00:23:31,800 --> 00:23:33,820
What are you going to do?

436
00:23:36,780 --> 00:23:38,140
 No. 

437
00:23:41,320 --> 00:23:43,680
 Stop. I was wrong. 

438
00:23:43,680 --> 00:23:46,420
 Director Gan, I'm sorry. 

439
00:23:49,220 --> 00:23:50,440
I thought someone was stalking me,

440
00:23:50,440 --> 00:23:51,720
but it was just a couple.

441
00:23:51,720 --> 00:23:53,200
"A couple"?

442
00:23:53,200 --> 00:23:54,920
Did you see who they were?

443
00:23:54,920 --> 00:23:57,840
It was so awkward. Why would I stay to find out?

444
00:23:57,840 --> 00:24:01,080
But it was right before dorm curfew.

445
00:24:01,080 --> 00:24:03,600
Were they still on a date?

446
00:24:03,600 --> 00:24:06,620
Don't they fear getting locked out?

447
00:24:22,300 --> 00:24:25,560
Isn't this situation resolved? Why are we still here?

448
00:24:25,560 --> 00:24:29,340
Look, the whole road is empty.

449
00:24:29,340 --> 00:24:31,920
Ding Zhi Tong will surely feel scared when she passes by.

450
00:24:31,920 --> 00:24:34,080
If someone's talking nearby, she won't fear.

451
00:24:34,080 --> 00:24:35,720
But we can't keep doing this forever.

452
00:24:35,720 --> 00:24:37,180
How long are we staying here?

453
00:24:37,180 --> 00:24:39,960
Shouldn't be too long. I already reported it to the school.

454
00:24:39,960 --> 00:24:43,080
Once they fix the streetlight, our job's done.

455
00:24:43,080 --> 00:24:44,560
You care about her so much.

456
00:24:44,560 --> 00:24:46,600
Why not just walk her back yourself?

457
00:24:46,600 --> 00:24:48,020
You think I don't want to?

458
00:24:48,020 --> 00:24:51,060
I don't want to appear too obvious and pressure her.

459
00:24:51,060 --> 00:24:53,620
Like that, no wonder you're still single.

460
00:24:58,420 --> 00:25:01,260
She's coming. Be ready.

461
00:25:06,660 --> 00:25:08,300
Say something.

462
00:25:08,300 --> 00:25:10,620
- About what? 
 - Like what you said before.

463
00:25:10,620 --> 00:25:12,140
Come on.

464
00:25:13,500 --> 00:25:14,700
I'm angry.

465
00:25:14,700 --> 00:25:16,840
- Don't hug me. 
 - Louder.

466
00:25:17,580 --> 00:25:19,240
Even louder.

467
00:25:19,240 --> 00:25:20,980
You scoundrel.

468
00:25:20,980 --> 00:25:22,920
- No, please. 
 - She's coming.

469
00:25:22,920 --> 00:25:25,000
- She's here. 
 - Don't kiss me.

470
00:25:25,000 --> 00:25:26,180
- She's right here. 
 - No.

471
00:25:26,180 --> 00:25:28,180
What are you two doing?

472
00:25:40,800 --> 00:25:42,820
Weren't you supposed to go that way?

473
00:25:42,820 --> 00:25:45,720
Who said I would come that way.

474
00:25:50,460 --> 00:25:51,740
So it was you two last night, too?

475
00:25:51,740 --> 00:25:53,580
- No. 
 - Yes.

476
00:26:01,060 --> 00:26:03,780
Your girlfriend is quite unique.

477
00:26:03,780 --> 00:26:05,640
It's so embarrassing.

478
00:26:11,320 --> 00:26:13,160
Your dorm is about to lock down, right?

479
00:26:13,160 --> 00:26:15,000
I'll walk you back.

480
00:26:15,000 --> 00:26:16,620
Okay.

481
00:26:19,740 --> 00:26:24,080
 So why did you ask the track team guys to test your shoes? 

482
00:26:24,080 --> 00:26:26,300
 It's hard to run an OEM business now. 

483
00:26:26,300 --> 00:26:29,380
 I told my mom we should transform 

484
00:26:29,380 --> 00:26:31,220
to develop our own R&amp;D.

485
00:26:31,220 --> 00:26:33,820
But she thinks OEM is already good enough.

486
00:26:33,820 --> 00:26:36,420
So I started experimenting on my own.

487
00:26:36,420 --> 00:26:37,780
I got them to try the shoes

488
00:26:37,780 --> 00:26:39,900
to collect performance data.

489
00:26:41,320 --> 00:26:43,540
But I never thought

490
00:26:43,540 --> 00:26:45,520
they'd be so mean.

491
00:26:49,220 --> 00:26:50,900
That's not your fault.

492
00:26:50,900 --> 00:26:53,260
Don't overthink it.

493
00:26:55,140 --> 00:26:58,180
So did you tear apart the shoes

494
00:26:58,180 --> 00:27:00,500
for research data too?

495
00:27:00,500 --> 00:27:03,380
Did you watch videos I posted online?

496
00:27:05,540 --> 00:27:09,700
In the future, I want to create my own sports shoe brand

497
00:27:09,700 --> 00:27:12,740
and build a sports science lab.

498
00:27:13,580 --> 00:27:17,560
Wang Yi? Wang Yi is a Ph.D. student in material science here.

499
00:27:17,560 --> 00:27:20,020
He is my research partner.

500
00:27:20,020 --> 00:27:22,240
You know what midsole material is?

501
00:27:22,240 --> 00:27:25,680
It's actually the core of a running shoe.

502
00:27:25,680 --> 00:27:27,460
That's what we are working on.

503
00:27:27,460 --> 00:27:31,460
Whether the brand works or not actually depends on that.

504
00:27:31,460 --> 00:27:33,260
Have you ever considered

505
00:27:33,260 --> 00:27:35,700
your main customer target group?

506
00:27:35,700 --> 00:27:39,460
For investment in a product or a company,

507
00:27:39,460 --> 00:27:41,900
the first detail is its target group.

508
00:27:41,900 --> 00:27:43,860
I've thought about that.

509
00:27:43,860 --> 00:27:47,360
Our brand mainly targets two groups:

510
00:27:47,360 --> 00:27:49,320
First are athletes.

511
00:27:49,320 --> 00:27:51,960
Second are running enthusiasts.

512
00:27:52,500 --> 00:27:54,740
But our focus is tech-driven running shoes.

513
00:27:54,740 --> 00:27:57,960
It helps athletes improve speed

514
00:27:57,960 --> 00:27:59,620
while keeping them safe.

515
00:27:59,620 --> 00:28:03,220
So you make shoes for people who love running.

516
00:28:03,220 --> 00:28:04,860
But have you ever thought,

517
00:28:04,860 --> 00:28:07,020
what if someone who doesn't like running

518
00:28:07,020 --> 00:28:09,080
puts on your shoes and enjoys it?

519
00:28:16,340 --> 00:28:18,100
You're right.

520
00:28:18,100 --> 00:28:21,160
If someone who hates running starts to love it

521
00:28:21,160 --> 00:28:23,560
after wearing the shoes I make,

522
00:28:23,560 --> 00:28:24,820
that's very meaningful.

523
00:28:24,820 --> 00:28:27,540
Exactly. That means your market gets wider.

524
00:28:27,540 --> 00:28:28,980
You'll make way more money.

525
00:28:28,980 --> 00:28:30,780
That's true.

526
00:28:30,780 --> 00:28:33,700
Then would you help me test the shoes?

527
00:28:33,700 --> 00:28:34,980
Me?

528
00:28:34,980 --> 00:28:36,320
Yes.

529
00:28:36,940 --> 00:28:38,520
Can I even do that?

530
00:28:38,520 --> 00:28:39,980
Why can't you?

531
00:28:39,980 --> 00:28:41,980
I'll take that as a yes then.

532
00:28:42,660 --> 00:28:44,100
When I finish my first pair of shoes,

533
00:28:44,100 --> 00:28:46,620
you'll be the very first one to test them.

534
00:28:46,620 --> 00:28:48,100
Deal.

535
00:28:58,280 --> 00:28:59,960
 Ding Zhi Tong, 

536
00:29:00,720 --> 00:29:03,120
 you must look amazing when you run. 

537
00:29:04,060 --> 00:29:06,020
