00:29:56,260 --> 00:29:58,020
Okay.

548
00:29:58,020 --> 00:29:59,720
I see.

549
00:30:01,360 --> 00:30:03,800
Then I'll see you tomorrow.

550
00:30:03,800 --> 00:30:06,940
All right, see you tomorrow.

551
00:30:08,180 --> 00:30:09,680
I'm leaving.

552
00:30:11,140 --> 00:30:12,740
Bye bye.

553
00:30:21,900 --> 00:30:24,620
Why are you still here?

554
00:30:24,620 --> 00:30:27,300
Why don't you go back?

555
00:30:27,300 --> 00:30:28,860
See you tomorrow.

556
00:30:28,860 --> 00:30:31,220
I'm leaving now. See you tomorrow.

557
00:30:31,220 --> 00:30:32,960
See you tomorrow.

558
00:30:33,500 --> 00:30:35,140
Which department are you from?

559
00:30:35,140 --> 00:30:37,200
 Why are you yelling so late? 

560
00:30:37,200 --> 00:30:38,880
 Running off? 

561
00:30:49,900 --> 00:30:52,900
Hello. I'm Ding Zhi Tong.

562
00:30:54,440 --> 00:30:56,500
Hello. Welcome to the interview.

563
00:30:56,500 --> 00:30:58,020
Please, have a seat.

564
00:30:58,900 --> 00:31:00,680
That's not quite right.

565
00:31:00,680 --> 00:31:02,460
Press palms together.

566
00:31:02,460 --> 00:31:04,920
Align the thumb webs, firm and steady.

567
00:31:04,920 --> 00:31:07,420
Hold for a second without shaking.

568
00:31:12,300 --> 00:31:16,420
Most importantly, look the person in the eye with confidence and sincerity.

569
00:31:18,620 --> 00:31:21,020
And don't forget to smile.

570
00:31:23,640 --> 00:31:25,140
It's just a handshake.

571
00:31:25,140 --> 00:31:27,120
I didn't know there was so much to it.

572
00:31:27,700 --> 00:31:30,400
It's actually the most important part of business etiquette.

573
00:31:30,400 --> 00:31:32,880
It sets the tone for your first impression.

574
00:31:32,880 --> 00:31:34,640
You really know your stuff.

575
00:31:34,640 --> 00:31:37,800
When it's my turn to interview, I definitely need your advice.

576
00:31:37,800 --> 00:31:39,720
Anytime.

577
00:31:39,720 --> 00:31:41,520
Can I take a look?

578
00:31:45,300 --> 00:31:47,460
Here's your lemon water. Enjoy.

579
00:31:47,460 --> 00:31:49,400
- Thanks. 
 - Thanks.

580
00:32:14,500 --> 00:32:16,660
What's wrong? It won't turn on?

581
00:32:16,660 --> 00:32:19,600
Yes. It happens a lot lately. I don't know what's wrong.

582
00:32:19,600 --> 00:32:22,100
I might really need to get it repaired.

583
00:32:23,840 --> 00:32:26,560
Let me see. I know how to fix it.

584
00:32:26,560 --> 00:32:28,880
Can you fix computers?

585
00:32:28,880 --> 00:32:29,960
Then take a look for me.

586
00:32:29,960 --> 00:32:31,632
- Sure. 
 - I really hope it can be fixed.

587
00:32:31,632 --> 00:32:33,980
I'd rather not replace it.

588
00:32:38,000 --> 00:32:39,960
Well?

589
00:32:39,960 --> 00:32:41,560
Is it fixable?

590
00:32:45,120 --> 00:32:47,620
What's the issue?

591
00:32:47,620 --> 00:32:50,760
Looks like it may have a hard drive problem.

592
00:32:50,760 --> 00:32:52,020
"Hard drive problem"?

593
00:32:52,020 --> 00:32:54,000
Are my files still there?

594
00:32:54,741 --> 00:32:58,380
Yes. But I might need to open it up to fix it.

595
00:32:59,020 --> 00:33:00,900
How... how about this?

596
00:33:00,900 --> 00:33:02,300
If you don't need to use it right now,

597
00:33:02,300 --> 00:33:05,360
I can take it home tonight, fix and return it tomorrow.

598
00:33:05,360 --> 00:33:07,360
Then I will have to trouble you with this.

599
00:33:07,360 --> 00:33:09,140
Thank you.

600
00:33:10,440 --> 00:33:12,160
No problem.

601
00:33:15,400 --> 00:33:17,940
Gan Yang, what happened that's so important?

602
00:33:17,940 --> 00:33:19,080
Finally, you're back.

603
00:33:19,080 --> 00:33:21,740
Thanks for your effort. Give me your bag.

604
00:33:21,740 --> 00:33:23,300
Sit.

605
00:33:23,300 --> 00:33:24,960
You must be thirsty. Have some water.

606
00:33:24,960 --> 00:33:26,280
Here.

